ResourceHeader.ResourceName: RBSP Energetic Particle, Composition, and Thermal Plasma Suite (ECT) Relativistic Electron Proton Telescope (REPT) Selenick Radiation Belt Proton Intensity Model, Level 3 (L3), Monthly Data

RevisionEvent.Note: Only known prior ReleaseDate of the metadata

Added DOI and PublicationInfo minted by LFB, updated InformationURL URLs as needed, updated the SPDF MetadataContact Person to Robert M. Candey, metadata updated to SPASE 2.4.1, reviewed by LFB 20220818

ResourceHeader.Description: The Files associated with the Van Allen Probes Selenick Model Data Product contain Model Radiation Belt Proton Intensity derived from Data taken by the Van Allen Probes REPT Instruments using the Method described by: Selesnick, R.S., Baker, D.N., Kanekal, S.G., Hoxie, V.C., and X. Li, (2018). Modeling the Proton Radiation Belt with Van Allen Probes Relativistic Electron-Proton Telescope Data. J. Geophys. Res.: Space Phys., 123. https://doi.org/10.1002/2017JA024661. Each File contains average Intensity, as a Function of Kinetic Energy, Equatorial Pitch Angle, and L-Shell, derived from one Month of Data.
